<subSubSection id="C31D6509FFD4FF88FF2CFE84FD54233A" pageId="28" pageNumber="529" type="description">
<paragraph id="8BB83682FFD4FF88FF2CFE84FDC22062" blockId="28.[151,1437,259,718]" box="[199,520,295,321]" pageId="28" pageNumber="529">
<emphasis id="B973EA90FFD4FF88FF2CFE84FE4A2062" bold="true" box="[199,384,295,321]" pageId="28" pageNumber="529">Measurements:</emphasis>
See 
<tableCitation id="C6850339FFD4FF88FE5DFE84FDC22062" box="[438,520,295,321]" captionStart="TABLE 1" captionStartId="8.[151,239,459,485]" captionText="TABLE 1. Measurements of specimens of Cypricercus sp. A., Cypricercus alfredo sp. nov. and Cypricercus tiao sp. nov. Values in brackets are only the lengths of spine (without the length of the valves)." pageId="28" pageNumber="529">Table 1</tableCitation>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BB83682FFD4FF88FF2CFEE8FD54233A" blockId="28.[151,1437,259,718]" pageId="28" pageNumber="529">
<emphasis id="B973EA90FFD4FF88FF2CFEE8FD832046" bold="true" box="[199,585,331,357]" pageId="28" pageNumber="529">Abbreviated diagnosis of female.</emphasis>
LV elongated, with dorsal margin almost straight and parallel to ventral margin; anterior margin less broadly rounded than in 
<taxonomicName id="4C074D01FFD4FF88FD57FED3FC8D20AA" authorityName="Martens &amp; Behen" authorityYear="1994" baseAuthorityName="Klie" baseAuthorityYear="1940" box="[700,839,368,394]" class="Ostracoda" family="Cyprididae" genus="Cypricercus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Podocopida" pageId="28" pageNumber="529" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="centrurus">
<emphasis id="B973EA90FFD4FF88FD57FED3FC8D20AA" box="[700,839,368,394]" italics="true" pageId="28" pageNumber="529">C. centrurus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and in 
<taxonomicName id="4C074D01FFD4FF88FC73FED3FBC220AA" authority="Almeida &amp; Ferreira &amp; Higuti &amp; Martens, 2021" authorityName="Almeida &amp; Ferreira &amp; Higuti &amp; Martens" authorityYear="2021" box="[920,1032,367,394]" class="Ostracoda" family="Cyprididae" genus="Cypricercus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Podocopida" pageId="28" pageNumber="529" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="alfredo" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis id="B973EA90FFD4FF88FC73FED3FBC220AA" box="[920,1032,367,394]" italics="true" pageId="28" pageNumber="529">C. alfredo</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis id="B973EA90FFD4FF88FBE5FECCFBAD20AA" bold="true" box="[1038,1127,367,393]" pageId="28" pageNumber="529">
<taxonomicNameLabel id="A24057EBFFD4FF88FBE5FECCFBAD20AA" box="[1038,1127,367,393]" pageId="28" pageNumber="529" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
RV also with dorsal margin almost straight and largely parallel to ventral margin, posterior spine almost as long as in 
<taxonomicName id="4C074D01FFD4FF88FB6DFE37FAD8208E" authorityName="Martens &amp; Behen" authorityYear="1994" baseAuthorityName="Klie" baseAuthorityYear="1940" box="[1158,1298,404,430]" class="Ostracoda" family="Cyprididae" genus="Cypricercus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Podocopida" pageId="28" pageNumber="529" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="centrurus">
<emphasis id="B973EA90FFD4FF88FB6DFE37FAD8208E" box="[1158,1298,404,430]" italics="true" pageId="28" pageNumber="529">C. centrurus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and equally centrally placed in the middle of the caudal margin, slightly pointing upwards, but less robust; almost twice as long as in 
<taxonomicName id="4C074D01FFD4FF88FF3AFE7FFE8B20D6" authority="Almeida &amp; Ferreira &amp; Higuti &amp; Martens, 2021" authorityName="Almeida &amp; Ferreira &amp; Higuti &amp; Martens" authorityYear="2021" box="[209,321,475,502]" class="Ostracoda" family="Cyprididae" genus="Cypricercus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Podocopida" pageId="28" pageNumber="529" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="alfredo" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis id="B973EA90FFD4FF88FF3AFE7FFE8B20D6" box="[209,321,475,502]" italics="true" pageId="28" pageNumber="529">C. alfredo</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis id="B973EA90FFD4FF88FEACFE78FE5520D6" bold="true" box="[327,415,475,501]" pageId="28" pageNumber="529">
<taxonomicNameLabel id="A24057EBFFD4FF88FEACFE78FE5520D6" box="[327,415,475,501]" pageId="28" pageNumber="529" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
Anterior calcified inner margin in both valves about twice the width of that in 
<taxonomicName id="4C074D01FFD4FF88FAEEFE7FFABF20D6" authority="Almeida &amp; Ferreira &amp; Higuti &amp; Martens, 2021" authorityName="Almeida &amp; Ferreira &amp; Higuti &amp; Martens" authorityYear="2021" box="[1285,1397,475,502]" class="Ostracoda" family="Cyprididae" genus="Cypricercus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Podocopida" pageId="28" pageNumber="529" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="alfredo" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis id="B973EA90FFD4FF88FAEEFE7FFABF20D6" box="[1285,1397,475,502]" italics="true" pageId="28" pageNumber="529">C. alfredo</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis id="B973EA90FFD4FF88FA90FE78FF02233A" bold="true" pageId="28" pageNumber="529">
<taxonomicNameLabel id="A24057EBFFD4FF88FA90FE78FF02233A" pageId="28" pageNumber="529" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
LV overlapping RV on all sides (
<figureCitation id="133C2A07FFD4FF88FDD5FE5CFD5B233A" box="[574,657,511,537]" captionStart="FIGURE 18" captionStartId="28.[151,250,1937,1961]" captionTargetBox="[293,1294,741,1914]" captionTargetId="figure-247@28.[293,1294,741,1914]" captionTargetPageId="28" captionText="FIGURE 18. Cypricercus sp. A. Upper Paraná River floodplain. A–F. Female. A. LVi. B. LVi, detail of anterior part. C. LVi, detail of posterior part. D. RVi. E. RVi, detail of anterior part. F. RVi, detail of posterior part. Scale bars: A, D: 1000 µm. B–C, E: 500 µm. F: 200 µm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4575045" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4575045/files/figure.png" pageId="28" pageNumber="529">Fig. 18</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C31D6509FFD4FF88FF2CFD80FC9C2342" pageId="28" pageNumber="529" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="8BB83682FFD4FF88FF2CFD80FC9C2342" blockId="28.[151,1437,259,718]" pageId="28" pageNumber="529">
<emphasis id="B973EA90FFD4FF88FF2CFD80FEF1231E" bold="true" box="[199,315,547,573]" pageId="28" pageNumber="529">Remarks.</emphasis>
We are convinced that this is a representative of a new species in the genus, but as we have only a single female, we will refrain from formally describing it here.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C31D6509FFD4FF88FF2CFDC8FADE23EE" pageId="28" pageNumber="529" type="biology_ecology">
<paragraph id="8BB83682FFD4FF88FF2CFDC8FADE23EE" blockId="28.[151,1437,259,718]" pageId="28" pageNumber="529">
<emphasis id="B973EA90FFD4FF88FF2CFDC8FE3123A6" bold="true" box="[199,507,619,645]" pageId="28" pageNumber="529">Ecology and Distribution.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName id="4C074D01FFD4FF88FDE9FDCFFD4023A5" authorityName="Almeida &amp; Ferreira &amp; Higuti &amp; Martens" authorityYear="2021" box="[514,650,620,646]" class="Ostracoda" family="Cyprididae" genus="Cypricercus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Podocopida" pageId="28" pageNumber="529" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B973EA90FFD4FF88FDE9FDCFFD4023A5" box="[514,650,620,646]" italics="true" pageId="28" pageNumber="529">Cypricercus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
sp. A was found associated with the root systems of 
<taxonomicName id="4C074D01FFD4FF88FB31FDCFFA8E23A6" box="[1242,1348,620,645]" class="Liliopsida" family="Pontederiaceae" genus="Eichhornia" kingdom="Plantae" order="Commelinales" pageId="28" pageNumber="529" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="azurea">
<emphasis id="B973EA90FFD4FF88FB31FDCFFA8E23A6" box="[1242,1348,620,645]" italics="true" pageId="28" pageNumber="529">E. azurea</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
located in a single lake of the Upper 
<collectingRegion id="49C3F860FFD4FF88FE36FD2CFDE3238A" box="[477,553,655,681]" country="Brazil" name="Parana" pageId="28" pageNumber="529">Paraná</collectingRegion>
River floodplain. Water temperature at time of collecting was 26.3°C; pH was basic (8); electrical conductivity was 66.2 µS. 
<superScript id="7C729BCAFFD4FF88FD7EFD10FD0223E2" attach="left" box="[661,712,691,717]" fontSize="6" pageId="28" pageNumber="529">cm-1</superScript>
and dissolved oxygen was 
<quantity id="4CFF9B67FFD4FF88FC17FD10FB8723ED" box="[1020,1101,691,718]" metricMagnitude="-6" metricUnit="kg" metricValue="9.4" pageId="28" pageNumber="529" unit="mg" value="9.4">9.4 mg</quantity>
. L- 
<superScript id="7C729BCAFFD4FF88FB84FD10FBBC23E2" attach="left" box="[1135,1142,691,705]" fontSize="6" pageId="28" pageNumber="529">1</superScript>
(see 
<tableCitation id="C6850339FFD4FF88FB5AFD10FACD23EE" box="[1201,1287,691,717]" captionStart="TABLE 2" captionStartId="27.[151,239,705,731]" captionTargetBox="[162,2004,826,1483]" captionText="TABLE 2. Localities and environmental characteristics from stations where the species Cypricercus sp. A., Cypricercus alfredo sp. nov. and Cypricercus tiao sp. nov. were collected. Bold: type locality of the new species. PAR = Paraná, ARA = Araguaia, AMA = Amazon, PAN = Pantanal, WT = water temperature, EC = electrical conductivity, DO = dissolved oxygen, CspA = Cypricercus sp. A, Ca = Cypricercus alfredo sp. nov., Ct = Cypricercus tiao sp. nov." httpUri="http://table.plazi.org/id/DF78660AFFD3FF8FFF7CFD62FAFD2200" pageId="28" pageNumber="529" tableUuid="DF78660AFFD3FF8FFF7CFD62FAFD2200">Table 2</tableCitation>
).
</paragraph>
